{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Legislation that could be considered this week would allow younger interstate truckers and undermine safety on roads and rails in numerous other ways.", "abstract": "Editorial warns that Senate bill Comprehensive Transportation and Consumer Protection Act of 2015, part of larger transportation legislative package, accedes to demands of trucking industry and will make highways less safe; points to provision that will reduce minimum age for interstate truck drivers to 18 as particularly dangerous; decries fact that legislation will not address concerns about safety defects in automobiles; underscores necessity of changing legislation before it is passed.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "26", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [], "original": "By THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "organization": "THE EDITORIAL BOARD"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/21/opinion/a-senate-bill-that-makes-roads-and-railroads-less-safe.html", "lead_paragraph": "Legislation that could be considered this week would allow younger interstate truckers and undermine safety on roads and rails in numerous other ways.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Making the Highways Less Safe", "main": "A Senate Bill That Makes Roads and Railroads Less Safe", "content_kicker": "Editorial", "kicker": "Editorial"}, "_id": "55adf2e338f0d84cf5633da4", "word_count": "566", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/07/21/opinion/21tues2/21tues2-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/07/21/opinion/21tues2/21tues2-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 746, "url": "images/2015/07/21/opinion/21tues2/21tues2-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/07/21/opinion/21tues2/21tues2-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "746"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/07/21/opinion/21tues